name: David di Michelangelo\Vv
description: David is a masterpiece of Renaissance sculpture, created in marble between 1501 and 1504 by the Italian artist Michelangelo. David is a 5.17-metre(17ft)marble statue of the Biblical figure David, a favoured subject in the art of Florence. The eyes of David, with a warning glare, were fixated towards 'Rome'.
